000) for Type Ia SNe with mid-range decline rates. The photometry exhibits\nnon-zero host extinction, with total A_V = 0.57 +/- 0.05 mag along the line of\nsight. NGC 1448, the host of SN 2001el, would be an excellent target for a\ndistance determination using Cepheids.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Oct 2002 17:49:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 21 Oct 2002 21:11:51 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 4 Nov 2002 18:54:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
